{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_013qKY3Pcb6pcgr4wEifycg1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete and verified — the oracle reports **\"Custom roles verified\" (exit 0)**.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe reporting dashboards were failing because of a misconfigured permissions change: `reporting-user` had been granted the `rawRead` role, which gave `find` on `appdb.raw` (the ingestion data that must stay private) but **no access at all** to `appdb.reports` (where dashboards read from).\n\nI restored the **minimum** access needed:\n\n1. **Created a read-only role** `reportingRole` on `appdb` with a single privilege: `find` on `appdb.reports` only.\n2. **Granted** `reportingRole` to `reporting-user`.\n3. **Revoked** the over-permissive `rawRead` role from `reporting-user`.\n\nVerified effective behavior for `reporting-user`:\n- ✅ Can read/aggregate `appdb.reports` (dashboards work again)\n- ✅ Denied reading `appdb.raw` (\"not authorized\") — ingestion data stays protected\n- ✅ Denied writing to `appdb.reports` — read-only, no excess privileges\n\nNo operators or CRDs were used; the change was made purely through MongoDB role administration."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":230,"cache_read_input_tokens":50164,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":230},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d808b3f3-d4e3-4ff0-9236-c4dab44afe1a","uuid":"94fdf793-8627-416f-b9b8-4fecc5f7bf1b","request_id":"req_011CcAiWupov7XPwJTVyaWa3"}
